Section 1. (A) As used in this section, "eligible 3
individual" means an individual who meets all of the following 4
criteria: 5
(1) The individual is between sixteen years of age and 6
thirty-five years of age at the time the Farming and Workforce 7
Development Program commences. 8
(2) The individual is a resident of this state. 9
(B) The Farming and Workforce Development Program is 10
hereby created, which shall provide training to eligible 11
individuals to prepare such individuals for seasonal crop 12
farming employment. Each county office of the Ohio State 13
University Extension and Central State University Extension 14
shall develop guidelines and policies for the application 15
process, training coursework, and implementation of the Program. 16
A person who has been convicted of or plead guilty to a 17
felony in this state or another state is eligible to participate 18
in the program so long as the person meets the definition of 19
"eligible individual." 20

